 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-77c","title":"Add dynamic shell completions with clap_complete","description":"## Overview

Implement dynamic shell completions using clap_complete with CompleteEnv for runtime completion generation. Provide seamless tab-completion for all commands, subcommands, flags, and dynamic values like worker IDs.

## Research Findings (2025-2026)

### clap_complete with CompleteEnv

Modern clap (v4.5+) supports dynamic completions via CompleteEnv:
- Runtime completion without pre-generated scripts
- Completes subcommands, flags, and arguments dynamically
- Works with bash, zsh, fish, powershell, elvish

**Cargo.toml:**
```toml
[dependencies]
clap = { version = "4.5", features = ["derive", "env"] }
clap_complete = { version = "4.5", features = ["unstable-dynamic"] }
```

### Dynamic Completion Setup

```rust
use clap::{Command, Parser};
use clap_complete::CompleteEnv;

fn main() {
    // Handle completion requests before normal execution
    CompleteEnv::with_factory(Cli::command).complete();

    // Normal CLI execution
    let cli = Cli::parse();
    // ...
}
```

### Shell Configuration

**Bash (~/.bashrc):**
```bash
source <(COMPLETE=bash rch)
```

**Zsh (~/.zshrc):**
```zsh
source <(COMPLETE=zsh rch)
```

**Fish (~/.config/fish/config.fish):**
```fish
COMPLETE=fish rch | source
```

**PowerShell:**
```powershell
Invoke-Expression (& rch --completions powershell | Out-String)
```

### Custom Value Completers

```rust
use clap::{Arg, ArgAction};
use clap_complete::ArgValueCompleter;

fn worker_completer(current: &std::ffi::OsStr) -> Vec<clap_complete::CompletionCandidate> {
    // Load worker IDs from config
    let workers = load_worker_ids().unwrap_or_default();
    workers
        .into_iter()
        .filter(|w| w.starts_with(&current.to_string_lossy().as_ref()))
        .map(|w| clap_complete::CompletionCandidate::new(w))
        .collect()
}

#[derive(Parser)]
struct Cli {
